column5: Now that was "Windy"!!      The "Last Laker"       Couple more Perching trips and then Bring on the 'Soft Water'   Rick
So you caught a laker,who hasnt this year. LOL That wind was nasty today. It was hard to light a smoke at break time..  Nice last outing Rick.   Simcoe is changing.
wish I got out today  nice going now come on open water
Glad you got one for your last outing Rick, way to go !!!
Way to go Rick,Tomorrow looks a lot lighter than todays wind.That works  for me .Thank goodness!!.
Yes, Brian, It has been a good Laker year!!  Season opener on the soft water will be interesting.  Davey A Perch day tomorrow?  Rick
I'm sure that will be the main menu,were in deep enough water so who knows.Just have to keep the Herring away lol.
Great day, great fish, great outdoors and great dinner,  enjoy and thanks for sharing the pics
Chillin' first shot Rick.  And a nice laker for your efforts too.  Good luck perchin' out the season.
